  / HTML: HTML
  %section#html
    %h1 HTML

    %h2 HyperText Markup Language

    %p
      The purpose of a web browser is to read
      %a( href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HTML" target="_blank" ) HTML
      documents and compose them into visible or audible web pages.

    %p The browser does not display the HTML tags, but uses the tags to interpret the content of the page.

    %p.align--bottom.text--center *We will be discussing HTML5. I won't even bore you with others.*

  / HTML: Tags
  %section#html-tags
    %h1 Tags

    %h3 HTML tags are used to label content.

    %p
      HTML is written in the form of
      %a( href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HTML_element" target="_blank" ) HTML elements
      consisting of tags.

    %p An HTML tag is composed of the name of the element, surrounded by angle brackets. Tags can be an opening and closing or self-closing (void elements).

    %p
      An
      %a( href="http://dev.w3.org/html5/spec-author-view/syntax.html#syntax-end-tag" target="_blank" ) end tag
      also has a slash after the opening angle bracket, to distinguish it from the
      = succeed "." do
        %a( href="http://dev.w3.org/html5/spec-author-view/syntax.html#syntax-start-tag" target="_blank" ) start tag

    %pre
