  %pre
    %code( data-trim="" )
      :preserve
        &lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
        &lt;html&gt;
          &lt;head&gt;
            information about the page
          &lt;/head&gt;
          &lt;body&gt;
            contents of the page
          &lt;/body&gt;
        &lt;/html&gt;

  %p
    The
    %strong header
    describes the page and the
    %strong body
    contains the page's contents.

  %p
    An HTML page is saved into a file ending with the extension
    %code .html

  %p
    %code DOCTYPE
    is telling the browser to interpret the page's code as HTML5.

