/ Tag: Block Elements vs Inline Elements
%section#block-vs-inline
  %h1 Block &amp; Inline

  %h2.text--left
    %a( href="http://htmlhelp.com/reference/html40/block.html" target="_blank" ) Block Elements

  %p Block elements contain an entire large region of content such as paragraphs, lists, or table cells. The browser places a margin of whitespace between block elements for separation.

  %h2.text--left
    %a( href="http://www.cs.sfu.ca/CC/165/sbrown1/wdgxhtml10/inline.html" target="_blank") Inline Elements

  %p
    Inline elements affect a small amount of content such as bold text, code fragments, or images. The browser allows many inline elements to appear on the same line.
    %strong They should be nested inside a block element.


