/ Tag: meta
%section#meta-data
  %h1
    Metadata:
    %a( href="http://www.w3schools.com/tags/tag_meta.asp" target="_blank" )
      %code &lt;meta&gt;

  %pre
    %code( data-trim="" )
      :preserve
        &lt;meta charset="utf-8"&gt;
        &lt;meta name="description" content="A presentation on HTML."&gt;
        &lt;meta name="keywords" content="java, textbook"&gt;

  %p
    Placed
    %strong
      in the
      %code head
    section of your HTML page. Information about your webpage (for a browser, search engine, etc.).

  %p
    %code meta
    tags often have both the
    %code name
    and
    %code content
    attributes. Some
    %code meta
    tags use the
    %code http-equiv
    attribute instead of
    = succeed "." do
      %code name

  %p
    The
    %code meta
    tag with
    %code charset
    attribute indicates language/character encodings.

  %p
    Using a
    %code meta
    tag
    %code Content-Type
    stops validator "tentatively valid" warnings.


